# =============================================================================
# tools.list — Declarative provisioning tool definitions
# =============================================================================
#
# FORMAT (pipe-delimited, 7 columns):
#   type | name | source | check | description | depends | options
#
# TYPES:
#   apt     Install via apt-get (source = package name)
#   snap    Install via snap    (source = package name)
#   github  Git clone from GitHub (source = "user/repo")
#   url     Download a file from a URL
#   script  Download and execute a shell script
#   manual  Cannot be automated — displayed as a manual step at the end
#
# CHECK  (how to verify the tool is already present; skip install if true):
#   -              Use the default check for this type:
#                    apt    → dpkg -s <source>
#                    snap   → snap list <name>
#                    github → directory from 'dir:' option exists
#                    url    → file from 'save:' option exists
#                    script → always attempt (use path: or cmd: override)
#   cmd:<shell>    Run a shell expression; exit 0 = already installed
#   path:<path>    Check if a file or directory exists (~ is expanded)
#
# DEPENDS (comma-separated tool names):
#   Listed tools must appear BEFORE this entry in the file.
#   If a dependency failed, this tool is skipped automatically.
#
# OPTIONS (semicolon-separated key:value pairs):
#   dir:<path>     github: clone destination   (default: ~/<repo-name>)
#   save:<path>    url:    destination file path
#   extract:<path> url:    unzip downloaded file into this directory
#   env:<K=V ...>  script: space-separated environment variables to prepend
#   args:<flags>   apt/snap/script: extra arguments for the install command
#   post:<cmd>     any type: shell command to run after successful install
#
# ORDERING: Tools are processed top-to-bottom. Place dependencies first.
# =============================================================================


# --- Core prerequisites (no dependencies) ------------------------------------
apt | curl        | curl              | -                          | HTTP client and file downloader                     | |
apt | wget        | wget              | -                          | Alternative file downloader                         | |
apt | git         | git               | -                          | Version control system                              | |
apt | unzip       | unzip             | -                          | ZIP archive extractor                               | |
apt | xclip       | xclip             | -                          | Clipboard command-line tool                         | |

# --- Shell -------------------------------------------------------------------
apt | zsh         | zsh               | -                          | Z shell — powerful bash alternative                 | |
apt | autojump    | autojump          | -                          | Fast directory navigation via 'j' command           | zsh |
apt | zsh-antigen | zsh-antigen       | -                          | Zsh plugin manager (apt package)                    | zsh |

# --- Editors, search & file tools --------------------------------------------
apt | vim         | vim               | -                          | Classic terminal text editor                        | |
apt | ag          | silversearcher-ag | cmd:which ag               | Fast code/text search (ag command)                  | |
apt | rg          | ripgrep           | cmd:which rg               | Fast code/text search — ripgrep (rg command)        | |
apt | bat         | bat               | cmd:which batcat           | Syntax-highlighted cat (binary is 'batcat' on Ubuntu) | |
apt | fzf         | fzf               | -                          | Fuzzy finder for files, history and more            | |
apt | eza         | eza               | -                          | Modern ls replacement with colors and icons         | |
apt | pcmanfm     | pcmanfm           | -                          | Lightweight graphical file manager                  | |

# --- System & desktop tools --------------------------------------------------
apt | htop        | htop              | -                          | Interactive process and resource monitor            | |
apt | xdotool     | xdotool           | -                          | X11 keyboard and mouse automation                   | |
apt | xbindkeys   | xbindkeys         | -                          | Custom keyboard shortcut manager                    | |
apt | colorize    | colorize          | -                          | Syntax colorizer for terminal output                | |
apt | tilix       | tilix             | -                          | Tiling terminal emulator                            | |

# --- Build tools & Python dev headers (needed to compile Python etc.) --------
apt | build-essential | build-essential | -                        | GCC, make and essential C/C++ build tools           | |
apt | libssl-dev  | libssl-dev        | -                          | OpenSSL development headers                         | |
apt | libbz2-dev  | libbz2-dev        | -                          | bzip2 compression development headers               | |
apt | libsqlite3-dev | libsqlite3-dev | -                          | SQLite3 development headers                         | |
apt | libffi-dev  | libffi-dev        | -                          | Foreign Function Interface development headers      | |
apt | libreadline-dev | libreadline-dev | -                        | GNU Readline development headers                    | |
apt | liblzma-dev | liblzma-dev       | -                          | LZMA/XZ compression development headers             | |

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
apt | python3-pip        | python3-pip               | -          | Python 3 package installer (pip3)                   | |
apt | python3-virtualenv | python3-virtualenv        | -          | Python 3 virtual environment tool                   | |
apt | python3-virtualenvwrapper | python3-virtualenvwrapper | -   | Convenient virtualenv commands: workon, mkvirtualenv | |

# --- Zsh ecosystem (requires zsh + git to be installed first) ----------------

# oh-my-zsh: the install script overwrites ~/.zshrc — our custom zshrc is
# copied AFTER all tools are installed (see setup_configs in provision.sh).
# RUNZSH=no  → don't exec zsh at the end (would pause the script)
# CHSH=no    → don't change the default shell (we do it explicitly later)
script | oh-my-zsh | https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh | path:~/.oh-my-zsh | Oh My Zsh framework and plugin manager | zsh,git | env:RUNZSH=no CHSH=no

# Fish-style autosuggestions plugin for zsh
github | zsh-autosuggestions | zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions | path:~/.zsh/zsh-autosuggestions | Fish-like command autosuggestions for zsh | zsh,git | dir:~/.zsh/zsh-autosuggestions

# Antigen plugin manager — sourced directly from ~/antigen.zsh in zshrc
# Note: git.io/antigen is deprecated; use the direct GitHub raw URL below
url | antigen | https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zsh-users/antigen/master/bin/antigen.zsh | path:~/antigen.zsh | Antigen zsh plugin manager (sourced as ~/antigen.zsh) | zsh | save:~/antigen.zsh

# --- Fonts -------------------------------------------------------------------

# Powerline patched fonts — provides "Ubuntu Mono for Powerline" and others.
# Required for the alien oh-my-zsh theme to render segment arrows correctly.
# The apt package (fonts-powerline) only ships the raw symbols font; the
# patched monospace fonts live in this GitHub repo.
# Check: "Ubuntu Mono derivative Powerline" present in fontconfig index.
github | powerline-fonts | powerline/fonts | cmd:fc-list | grep -q "for Powerline" | Powerline-patched monospace fonts (Ubuntu Mono for Powerline etc.) | git | dir:/tmp/powerline-fonts;post:/tmp/powerline-fonts/install.sh

# --- Manual steps (cannot be fully automated) --------------------------------
manual | pycharm | https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/download/ | - | Download PyCharm and extract to ~/programy/pycharm/ (required for pycharm.desktop entry) | |
manual | firefox-plugins | - | - | Configure Firefox plugins: Tree Style Tabs, Multi-Account Containers | |
manual | ssh-key | https://github.com/settings/keys | - | Add your SSH public key (~/.ssh/id_*.pub) to GitHub/GitLab | |
